HEADWORD: Anemography
<hw>An`e*mog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a`nemos</grk> wind + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
description of the winds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art of recording the direction and force of the
wind, as by means of an anemograph.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anemology</ent>⟦br⟧
